org.apache.taverna.reference.impl.external.http

Class HttpReference

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.reference.AbstractExternalReference
      • org.apache.taverna.reference.impl.external.http.HttpReference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, ExternalReferenceSPI

    public class HttpReference
extends AbstractExternalReference
implements ExternalReferenceSPI
    Implementation of ExternalReference used to refer to data held in a locally accessible file. Inherits from AbstractExternalReference to enable hibernate based persistence.

      • openStream

        public InputStream openStream(ReferenceContext context)
                       throws DereferenceException
        Return the data at the URL represented by this external reference
        Specified by:
        openStream in interface ExternalReferenceSPI
        Parameters:
        context - the ReferenceContext object used to obtain e.g. security agents or other facilities required when de-referencing this reference.
        Returns:
        an InputStream providing access to the referenced data
        Throws:
        DereferenceException - if the reference cannot be de-referenced. This may be because of problems with the context such as security failures, or it may be because the reference is inherently not possible to de-reference (as in the case of a non-serializable API consumer reference).
